## PRE-TESTING SETUP

### Environment
- [ ] Node.js v18+ installed
- [ ] npm dependencies installed: `npm install`
- [ ] `.env.local` file configured with Firebase credentials
- [ ] Git repository clean

### Build Verification
- [ ] `npm run build` succeeds without errors
- [ ] No TypeScript compilation errors: `tsc --noEmit`
- [ ] Dev server starts: `npm run dev`
- [ ] No console errors on startup

---

## SECURITY TESTING

### Firestore Rules Validation
- [ ] Access firestore.rules in Firebase Console
- [ ] Verify RBAC rules are in place
- [ ] Test unauthenticated access (should fail)
- [ ] Test authenticated admin access (should succeed)
- [ ] Test role-based restrictions

### Credentials Protection
- [ ] Verify .env file not in git history
- [ ] Check .gitignore includes .env
- [ ] Verify .env.example has placeholder values
- [ ] No API keys in source code files

### Authentication Flow
- [ ] Login with valid Firebase credentials works
- [ ] Login with invalid credentials shows error
- [ ] Logout clears user state
- [ ] Session persists on page refresh
- [ ] Proper error messages shown to user

